00:26:26.346 --> 00:26:27.296 A:middle
You don't have to reach out and

00:26:27.296 --> 00:26:28.256 A:middle
try and aim for it on the

00:26:28.256 --> 00:26:28.726 A:middle
screen.

00:26:29.036 --> 00:26:30.906 A:middle
You just move close to it, and

00:26:30.906 --> 00:26:31.716 A:middle
when you want to fire the

00:26:31.716 --> 00:26:33.516 A:middle
slingshot, you just pull back

00:26:33.516 --> 00:26:34.016 A:middle
and release.

00:26:35.056 --> 00:26:37.046 A:middle
So, it's incredibly precise,

00:26:37.046 --> 00:26:38.516 A:middle
because you can fire in three

00:26:38.836 --> 00:26:39.386 A:middle
dimensions.

00:26:39.386 --> 00:26:40.366 A:middle
You have three dimensions of

00:26:40.366 --> 00:26:41.976 A:middle
precision while you're moving

00:26:41.976 --> 00:26:42.886 A:middle
that slingshot, while you're

00:26:42.886 --> 00:26:43.546 A:middle
pulling it back.

00:26:44.256 --> 00:26:45.406 A:middle
And, that's more than you could

00:26:45.406 --> 00:26:47.156 A:middle
ever do using touch.

00:26:47.686 --> 00:26:49.196 A:middle
So, moving your device, it's not

00:26:49.196 --> 00:26:50.786 A:middle
only really natural, but it's

00:26:50.786 --> 00:26:52.866 A:middle
also more precise than you could

00:26:52.866 --> 00:26:57.836 A:middle
ever do using touch in AR apps.

